Bakrie & Brothers, Krakatau, Medco: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-12-09T01:40:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/bakrie-brothers-krakatau-medco-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have  unusual (JCI)  moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The Jakarta Composite index fell 0.3 percent to 3,781.76.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures dropped 2.1 percent to
$98.34 a barrel in New York yesterday, the lowest settlement
since Nov. 28. Oil was last at $98.36 a barrel.  PT Medco Energi
Internasional (MEDC)  , Indonesia’s biggest listed oil company,
fell 2 percent to 2,425 rupiah and  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  , the second biggest, lost 0.7 percent to 154 rupiah.  PT Bakrie & Brothers (BNBR)  : The investment company
expects the divestment of three units to be completed in the
first half of 2012, Bisnis Indonesia reported, citing President
Director Bobby Gafur. Bakrie & Brothers rose 4 percent to 52
rupiah.  PT Bakrie Sumatera Plantations (UNSP)  : The palm oil
producer will build a 15.5-megawatt power plant next year to
replace the current diesel-fired plant which may reduce energy
costs by as much as 40 percent, Kontan reported, without saying
where it obtained the information. Bakrie Sumatera was unchanged
at 275 rupiah.  PT Krakatau Steel (KRAS)  : Indonesia’s largest steel
producer has allocated $400 million to $450 million for capital
expenditure next year to increase output and build a blast
furnace, Bisnis Indonesia reported, citing Finance Director
Sukandar. The company set aside $350 million to $550 million for
capital expenditure this year, according to the report. Krakatau
was unchanged at 830 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  